# Nous Core Manifest (nous-specific additions)
#
# Entries inherited from ariadne live in nous/ariadne-base.manifest, which is
# processed first by setup.sh. This file holds only nous's own additions.
#
# Format: <action> <source-path> [<target-path>]
#
# Actions:
#   symlink   — create symlink (or copy in vendor mode)
#   copy      — copy once (for files that need local modification)
#   scaffold  — create empty directory
#   touch     — create empty file if missing
#   merge     — JSON merge (settings.ariadne.json layered under settings.local.json)

# ── Nous skills ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
symlink   nous/skills/nous-tools    .claude/skills/nous-tools
symlink   nous/skills/charon        .claude/skills/charon

# ── Makefile ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
symlink   Makefile.nous

# ── Documentation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
copy      README.md           README-NOUS.md

# ── Directory conventions ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
scaffold  life
scaffold  memory/ideas/pensive
scaffold  memory/life/travel
scaffold  memory/life/references
scaffold  memory/work/meeting-notes
